summary: pokemon! au knk: (5/5)                     ↳ Kim Jihun (small headcanons under the cut, but you can see the names of the...
caption:
pokemon! au knk: (5/5)

                   ↳ Kim Jihun

(small headcanons under the cut, but you can see the names of the pokemons, by the order on the gif, in the caption)

             ⋆ It’s not a real surprise to know that, just like Jihun, his pokemons also love staying on the floor.

            ⋆ Jihun actually likes to try to create multiple new movements, so mostly of time his pokes are just 100% done with him.

            ⋆ And that’s how he ended up with frozen pipes, and Glaceon still isn’t sorry for it.

            ⋆ Persian is actually his main, so this is usually why he gets away with all the things that he knocks off in the middle of the night. And with all the timess he used Amnesia to make Jihun feed him twice.

            ⋆ They all actually have a big and wonderful connection, with Jihun and his pokemons knowing exactly what they can or can’t do, in and out of battles.

            ⋆ Their battle style is literally like a dance, beautiful, harmonizing and that will distract you enough to make you not noticed their attack strategy and, well, you’re defeated.

            ⋆ Oricorio and Kirlia are the ones that often dance with him, around the house while they (try) to clean it, on actual competitions, or just to play with the small Roselia.

            ⋆ That often gets irritated that she can’t follow all the steps perfectly and just end up using Sunlight and almost blinding everyone.

            ⋆ Mienshao often just stays back judging his friends, but sometimes he tries to teach some fighting moves for them. At least until Glaceon tried to bite one of his sleeves.

            ⋆ They always have a day reserved for train dance and fight moves, which results in them all stopped in the living room imitating what could be a scene from Karate Kid.

summary: My favorite Pokemon from each Type: Grass:Tsareena(I love her since it reveals her evolution) Fire:Arcanine(My favorite since I...
caption:
My favorite Pokemon from each Type:

Grass:Tsareena(I love her since it reveals her evolution)

Fire:Arcanine(My favorite since I was a kid)

Water:Blastoise(My favorite final evolution starter)

Normal:Eevee(Yep,I’m Team Eeevee)

Electric:Luxray(I remember using Luxray in Platinum)

Psychic:Mega Gardevoir(My favorite from Gen 3)

Fighting:Lopunny(I love her Mega Evolution so much)

Rock:Rockruff(When I saw this cutie,I died from cuteness!!)

Ground:Flygon(I remember using Flygon in Black 2,and I love Flygon so much)

Flying:Staraptor(From the flying type Pokemon I used,Staraptor turns one of my favorite Bird Pokemon in Gen 4)

Bug:Pheromosa(Bug Type is my least favorite,but Phermosa turns one of my favorite UB from Gen 7)

Poison:Salazzle(When I react to Salandit and the new ability Corrosion,I totally fell in love with it’s final Evolution Salazzle,where should we get the male evolution for Salandit Gamefreak!!)

Dark:Zorua(Absol was one of my favorite Dark type Pokemon,but Zorua stole my heart,I remember I got a Zorua in Black 2 and always disguise as Flygon XD)

Ghost:Mimikyu(When I saw Mimikyu for the first time,I react to the design and I got scared on Acerola’s Island Challenge,but at least it becomes popular,even appears in Smash Bros Ultimate)

Ice:Lapras(Ice type is one of my favorite types along with Water and Dragon,and Lapras is my absolute favorite from Gen 1,even I use Lapras in Pokemon Stadium so much)

Steel:Empoleon(One of my favorite Gen 4 Starters,Empoleon,I remember using Empoleon in Platinum,and also appears in Pokken Tournament)

Dragon:Garchomp(My absolute favorite Dragon type,even I saw a Halloween special of a Latino News and they were dressed as Pokemon and an Actress dressed as a Sexy Garchomp)

Fairy:Alolan Ninetails(Other favorite Pokemon from Gen 1,and is Alolan Ninetails,It becomes so popular in Gen 7,even I saw some merchandise of Alolan Vulpix)

summary: Squirtwig, Wartle and Blasterra Squirtle and Turtwig, Wartortle and Grotle and Blastoise and Torterra fusion Squirtwig is a...
caption:
Squirtwig, Wartle and Blasterra

Squirtle and Turtwig, Wartortle and Grotle and Blastoise and Torterra fusion

Squirtwig is a water Type

Wartle and Blasterra are Water/Grass Type

All have Torrent as their normal Ability.

All have Thick Fat as their Hidden Ability.

Stats:

Squirtwig: HP - 50, Atk - 58, Def - 70, SpA - 55, SpD - 67, Spe - 40

Wartle: HP - 66, Atk - 75, Def - 90, SpA - 65, SpD - 73, Spe - 45

Blasterra: HP - 88, Atk - 110, Def - 115, SpA - 95, SpD - 100, Spe - 67

Squirtwig - The Young Bubble Pokemon

Wartle - The Water Sprinkler Pokemon

Blasterra - The Tree Fountain Pokemon

Squirtwig is very playful and shoots out bubbles from the stick on its head. These bubbles have been infused with a special sap which means that they do not pop. Having a field of Squirtwig blowing bubbles under the sunset can be a magnificent display.

Wartle is used for many agricultural jobs as it can squirt water out of the little holes on the stick on its back. Its back is almost like a bucket and can hold some water but it is usually very clumsy and will spill water from it.

Blasterra has full control of the water that it gathers from the rain and uses it to hydrate itself and create a constant supply of water that others can drink from. There is a regular competition annually in which people will show off the wooden fountain on their Blasterra’s back and it will be judged for the nicest looking one. 

Request for @quagsi. I hope you like it! I spent way too long on Blastera’s tree fountain thing; that took ages for me to be happy with it. I’m finally satisfied with the outcome.

Squirtwig is very playful and shoots out bubbles from the stick on its head. These bubbles have been infused with a special sap which means that they do not pop. Having a field of Squirtwig blowing bubbles under the sunset can be a magnificent display.

Wartle is used for many agricultural jobs as it can squirt water out of the little holes on the stick on its back. Its back is almost like a bucket and can hold some water but it is usually very clumsy and will spill water from it.

Blasterra has full control of the water that it gathers from the rain and uses it to hydrate itself and create a constant supply of water that others can drink from. There is a regular competition annually in which people will show off the wooden fountain on their Blasterra’s back and it will be judged for the nicest looking one. 

Request for @quagsi. I hope you like it! I spent way too long on Blastera’s tree fountain thing; that took ages for me to be happy with it. I’m finally satisfied with the outcome.

summary: I glance at the roof of the cave just in time to see it come crashing down towards me with an ominous rumble. Laurel grabs me...
body:
I glance at the roof of the cave just in time to see it come crashing down towards me with an ominous rumble. Laurel grabs me with her vines and starts to yank me out of the way, but I know there’s not enough time. I brace myself for the impact, cursing the fact that my rescue mission is ending with being crushed by boulders in Mount Moon without having ever accomplished anything.


 Will Tessa actually be crushed by boulders in Mount Moon without having ever accomplished anything? Find out in Chapter 8 of The Scientist!

summary: Is the fruit that grows on the chin of a Tropius actual fruit? Can they be eaten? Or are they just a growth that looks like...
question: Is the fruit that grows on the chin of a Tropius actual fruit? Can they be eaten? Or are they just a growth that looks like fruit? Any other tidbits on Tropius?
answer:
Yes, tropius chin fruit is real fruit; tropius naturally drop the fruits twice a year and regrow them, but the fruits can be picked before then with no harm to the tropius. They are actually a cousin of the common nanab berry– they are a species of nanab that almost went extinct due to a plague, but were saved because they grow around tropius necks. As of now, they are still unable to be grown, but as long as they grow around tropius they will survive for the future.

Tropius are the oldest species of non-fossil pokémon (defined as pokémon which went extinct but have been resurrected in modern times), having been around as we would recognize them since around 230 million years ago. Complete tropius fossils are rare, however.

Although tropius are their own species, they belong to the same clade as the chikorita line.

Tropius are social creatures; they form herds and care for their young for many years after they hatch. It is uncommon for tropius to leave their herds even after reaching adulthood, and tropius with trainers should be allowed to return home to visit their herds at least twice a year, around when their fruit is ready to drop.
